<h2>How to generate CSV data correctly</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    File must be <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">UTF-8</a> encoded. Follow <a href="https://www.webtoffee.com/how-to-save-csv-excel-file-as-utf-8-encoded/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">this link for example</a> to read instruction how to save as UTF-8.
  </li>
  <li>First row is reserved for column names</li>
  <li>Column names are case insensitive meaning that "Title" column, could be also named as "title", "TITLE" etc.</li>
  <li>File can contain extra columns, if column is not recognized by importing script it will be omitted</li>
  <li>Id column is required for all files. To add new entities leave it empty, to update it must contain matching entity Id from the database</li>
  <li>
    Make sure you generate .csv file using comma (,) separator. Some computers will generate .csv files where values are separated by semicolons (;) instead of commas (,).
    <a href="https://harvestmedia.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360023978031-Opening-Excel-files-with-the-correct-CSV-list-separator" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Take a look here</a>
  </li>
</ul>

